post_text:
Attention: All 6th and 7th-grade students

If you have not signed up for a sport or you are thinking of going out for a sport, you might want to think about USMS Cross Country. Go to Final Forms and fill out the necessary forms. I will then contact you and your parents and give them information about the season. Things are up in the air right now about Fall sports but be ready if we are a go in August.
If you already signed up for the 2020 USMS Cross Country team, then fill out the Final Forms paperwork. I will get you info once I know what the season will look like for the fall.
If you or your parents have any questions email me at jeff_f@usevs.org and I will respond as soon as I can.
If you join then I will also keep you up to date on the sports season and how it will be handled during this uncertain time.

Thank you,
Coach Fett

*USEVS Loaner Chromebook Return Announcement*

Today from 4pm-8pm and tomorrow from 10am-2pm are the FINAL TWO DAYS to return a USEVS Loaner Chromebook!! Failure to do so will result in a school fee assessment for the replacement cost of the device!!

The drop-off location will be at Upper Sandusky High School, using the east-side gymnasium doors (same doors as the pick-up program). We will use the same “drive-thru” method, meaning you do NOT need to get out of your car. Enter via Houpt Drive entrance and travel north to the gym doors. You can come on any of the days that work best for you!

Please bring the following items with you when you come to return your loaner device:
Chromebook
Chromebook charger

Returning the device carries the acknowledgment of the following:

I agree that:
I understand that once the condition of my returned device is assessed by the Technology Department if there is any damage that appears to be caused by vandalism, abuse or misuse may result in repair charges being assessed.

Please email Mr. Frye at jim_f@usevs.org if you have any questions!

Upper Sandusky High School and SportsCare at Wyandot Memorial Hospital are partnering to offer athletic physicals June 8 to 12 for high school and middle school athletes entering grades 7-12.

WMH medical professionals will provide physical exams for a $15 donation to the USHS Athletic Department. The money raised will help purchase supplies for district teams.

The physicals will be held from 3-6 p.m. by appointment only with two athletes scheduled every 15 minutes to provide for separation and safety. The athletes are required to bring a mask and wear it during the exam, and are encouraged to have completed and printed out the physical packet from Final Forms. These forms with parent…

shared_text:
Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
May 15 at 8:52 AM ·

From Athletic Director Brad Ehrman:

Wyandot Memorial Hospital has announced that its annual USHS/USMS Athletic Physical Day usually held in late May has been canceled as of now. They are looking at possible reschedule options and also athletic physical options at the hospital.

Students needing new physicals should contact their primary care physician or a certified physician of their choice to receive a new physical if needed. OHSAA PPE Physical Forms can be printed off from each student's Final Forms account and taken to their certified physician at the time of the physical appointment. OHSAA athletic physicals are currently valid for 13 months.

Any questions, please email Brad Ehrman at brad_e@usevs.org!

*USEVS Loaner Chromebook Return Announcement*

The district Loaner Chromebook RETURN days have been scheduled for Tuesday/Thursday, May 26th/28th from 4pm-8pm, and Wednesday/Friday, May 27th/29th from 10am-2pm.

The drop-off location will be at Upper Sandusky High School, using the east-side gymnasium doors (same doors as the pick-up program). Please email Mr. Frye at jim_f@usevs.org if you have any questions!

South Impact
May 1 at 8:10 PM ·

It is with a heavy heart that we reach out to you tonight to share some sad news. Mrs. Norris, who was the secretary at South, has passed away. This is a hard time for all of us and we have lost a well loved member of our school family. A mailbox will be located on the front porch at South Elementary if you wish to place notes or cards for the family. Counseling and grief resources for parents will be posted on the USEVS home page and Facebook page. Thank you so much for your thoughts and prayers at this very hard time, as Rams, we are all mourning.

post_text:
We hope that you and your families are safe and healthy during these unprecedented times. As you may have suspected, the PBIS Fundraiser that was originally scheduled to occur at the Elks in Upper Sandusky on March 22nd has now been cancelled. Like many of you, we were hoping that we’d be able to reschedule this event, but due to the ongoing health crisis and various mandated health orders by the state, we are not able to host the event.

We’d like to thank everyone who donated food items, bought tickets, or donated gift baskets. We truly appreciate your support of our students and our school. Anyone who purchased tickets can inquire about a full refund by contacting the USMS student ticket salesperson or by contacting Paul Mates via email at paul_m@usevs.org. *Please note that the school cannot refund any money that was not turned into the school office or Mr. Mates. Also, if requesting a refund is not completed by May 18th, no refund will or can be issued due to the end of the school year. Thank you for your understanding in this matter. Stay safe and GO RAMS!

shared_text:
Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
May 1 at 8:20 AM ·

Following Governor DeWine's order to close school facilities through June 30th, the OHSAA sent out the following directive in regard to the extension of the current no contact period. The no contact period, meaning no school activities can take place and there is to be no in-person instruction between athletes and coaches, is now extended through May 31st. The reason OHSAA did not go ahead and extend the no contact period through June 30th is to allow flexibility in case the June 30th facility closure is lifted early. As the May 31st date gets closer, if the June 30th facility closure remains intact, then OHSAA will extend their no contact period through that date as well, or as long as school facilities are closed. Information for Fall athletes entering grades 7-12 to sign up for their respective sport, coach contact information, and FinalForms completion for the 20-21 school year will be posted later today. Thank you for your patience in these unprecedented times.

Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
March 30 at 4:03 PM ·

Good afternoon! This is Laurie Vent, Superintendent of Upper Sandusky Schools.

I’m writing today to inform any parent who successfully signed up for our Chromebook Loaner Program that we are ready to distribute them tomorrow, Tuesday, March 31st outside the front High School Gymnasium doors. When you signed up, you chose a 2-hour window of time that you felt best worked for you, so please arrive during your selected time. Times are – 8am-10am, 10am-12pm, 12pm-2pm and 6pm-8pm. If you cannot make your time slot, feel free to come anytime. Please enter the High School front parking lot from the south entrance off Houpt Drive and continue north so your driver’s side window is next to the curb for easy pickup purposes in front of the HS Gymnasium doors.

For parents who did not get signed up in time for Round 1 Tuesday pickup, tomorrow night we will be posting on our district website, social media and sending a mass parent email with the link to sign up for Round 2.

Hope everyone is safe and healthy in your homes! Thank you!

Ohio Department of Education
March 27 at 6:16 PM ·

📺📝📚 Working together to support Ohio's students!

Beginning Monday, March 30, Ohio’s eight PBS stations will air grade-level appropriate, standards-based programs for students as part of their new #LearnAtHome initiative. Check your local listings for the full schedule.

The educational teams at each station will provide additional resources related to the new programming schedule.

Visit http://pbslearningmedia.org to access free online resources for educators and students.

The Ohio Broadcast Educational Media Commission shares more details here: https://broadcast.ohio.gov/Portals/0/Images/ProjectSpotlight/OhioPublicBroadcastersUnite_NewsRelease_3_26_2020.pdf

#InThisTogetherOhio #OhioEd

USEVS Chromebook Loaner Program

Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
March 26 at 2:05 PM ·

The district has begun preparing for our Chromebook Loaner Program, to begin sometime next week (week of March 30th). Details will be announced early next week via a phone call alert from Mrs. Vent, and, the information will also be posted on the district website, social media, and SchoolMessenger mass email.

If you have already signed up previously, please do NOT sign up again! Your submissions were recorded and registered. If you have not signed up previously, use the URL below to do so. If you need more than one Chromebook, you need to submit individually for each request.

Two requirements for this program: 1) You have access to WiFi network somewhere (Chromebooks require Wifi), 2) you don't have a device(s) at home now, or that work like Chromebook does at school.

Thank you!

Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
March 24 at 11:02 AM ·

Open Enrollment Information:

There are two kinds of open enrollment in our district:

INTRA-district open enrollment is for families with K-5 students who live WITHIN the Upper Sandusky School district and wish to have their K-5 child attend a different building than the one they are assigned based on address.

INTER-district open enrollment is for families with students of any grade level who do NOT live within the Upper Sandusky school district borders but wish to attend Upper Sandusky schools.

Open enrollment must be applied for each year.

If you are a CURRENT open enrolled family of either type, you will be mailed a form for each child. Please complete the form(s) and mail them back to:

Linda Barth, 800 N. Sandusky Ave., Suite A, Upper Sandusky OH 43351.

If you are wanting to apply for open enrollment for the FIRST time ever, please call the central office at 419-294-2306 and leave a message with your name, address, which type of form you need and how many (1 per school-age child). The form(s) will be mailed to you.

Upper Sandusky E.V. Schools (OH)
March 22 at 5:26 PM ·

Due to the Governor's decision of a "stay-at-home" order, USEVS will be taking the following course of action:

1. All buildings will be CLOSED - no pick-up or drop-off will take place until further notice. Someone will be in the office on Tuesdays from 8am-12pm for phone calls only.
2. Chromebook loaner program has been postponed until further notice.
3. "Grab-and-Go Brunch Bags" will continue on Tuesday and Thursday with limited drop off opportunities at USHS (north lot) and South ES (parking lot) from 11am-12:30pm.

We urge you to remain safe during this time and to do your best at assisting your children. Teachers can be reached via email. Our teachers are eager to help you in any way they can. Click the link to search for teacher email addresses: http://www.usevs.org/DistrictContacts.aspx

Please be patient during this time frame and do what is best to keep everyone safe. Thank you!

post_text: Mrs. Newell's coding course ended the semester with a Breakout EDU challenge with Mark & Nancy Johnson! Breakout EDU games require students to use critical thinking, collaboration, creativity, and communication.
shared_text:
Team Newell ELA
January 10 at 6:14 PM ·

Teamwork makes the Dream Work! Coding students ended the semester course by playing a Breakout EDU game with Mark and Nancy Johnson from The First Citizens National Bank!! Nancy’s team was the winner! Mark’s team also broke into the box by solving 5 different puzzles to unlock a padlock, 3 digit lock, color lock, word lock, and 4 digit lock. Mark and Nancy shared the importance of teamwork at FCNB and encouraged students to develop these skills for their futures.

post_text: 6th graders are implementing challenges this year to develop a safe, kind, fun learning environment at Union Middle School! We are the RAMS!
shared_text:
Team Newell ELA
November 6, 2019 at 7:07 PM ·

Even though many of my students told me that they were scared to death, they took on our 1st challenge of the year. (Do not save seats in class or at lunch. Avoid cliques and befriend ALL- Sit at a new table each day or sit with someone new each day.) As I walked around the lunchroom, I received smiles, waves, and thumbs up which made me very proud to be their teacher. They tried something new even though it made them feel VERY uncomfortable!!!! Mrs. Parrot noticed a change in cafeteria behavior and rewarded them with games in the auditorium! Since there are over 100+ students in the sixth grade, we will continue this challenge for months to come so they will have the chance to meet many classmates and to sit at all the different tables in the cafeteria! My hope is that this will become a habit this year! We will implement 29 more challenges throughout the year which were adapted and inspired by Ron Clark's 55 Essential Rules.

post_text: Compound Sentences and Kahoot Team Mode
shared_text:
Team Newell ELA
October 26, 2019 at 2:23 PM ·

Did you know a compound sentence contains at least two independent clauses and can be joined by a coordinating conjunction (for, and, nor, but, or, yet, so)? On Friday, sixth-graders played Kahoot in team mode to apply their knowledge! Next week, complex sentences will be the focus! Soon students will be able to vary sentence structure while they write about Reading!

post_text: The First Citizens National Bank is at it again! They are teaming up with Mrs. Newell to help prepare her students for the future! Year # 8
shared_text:
Team Newell ELA
October 20, 2019 at 10:47 PM ·

Shelby Rice from The First Citizens National Bank helped kick off year #8 of our community partnership ❤️ Even though my students are only 11-12 years old, we are teaming together to prepare them for the workplace. On Friday, we focused on teamwork (Tower of Feetsa Activity)and communication (Survive on the Moon Activity). Shelby shared how she uses these skills while working at FCNB, and she also explained what could happen if an employee did not develop these skills. Thank you Shelby for a fantastic Friday!
